storyInfo: Istina is uncharacteristically focused on decorating the Ursus Student Self-Government Group's booth at the food festival. What's motivating her to go all out?

attributes.content: Anna, do you know what time it is?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Anna!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Sonya, you can see I've been assembling my outfit. The clock's behind you. You have the power to look for yourself.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: It's already twenty 'til!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Your warning is appreciated.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Yeah, I AM warning you!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I did tell you how strenuous it is to coordinate an outfit, and that it could take a very long time. If you're hungry, you can go to the canteen for lunch, and I'll head there myself once I'm done.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Do you really need to do all this just for some food festival booth?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Sure, you're manning it, so you wanna dress up a little. But do you have to take this long? It's already been half an hour.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Is half an hour so long?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: It's not short.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: It's worth taking the time to ensure we match well with the theme of our booth.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: And that theme is 'Ursus Desserts'. That's it.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Like, we're Ursus from Ursus, even if we're wearing plain old Rhodes Island uniforms, we're gonna fit the theme. How are you still working on this?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: If you're going to be so impatient, you don't have to be here.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Hmph. Fine. I'll go eat.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I know you're reading your book there because you want to keep me company. You don't want to leave me alone
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But there's no need to force yourself, Sonya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Want me to bring you something to eat?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: No thank you. I'll go to the canteen myself in a moment.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I'm bac—
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Anna... why are you still screwing around with your clothes?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I'm almost finished. I only need about ten more minutes, barring any calamities. All that's left is a hairband to settle on.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Slow down there, speedy. Don't give me whiplash.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Sonya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: You done?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: What do you think of this hairband? It goes well with the ensemble, but isn't it too plain?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Can you just tell me what you want already?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I think we can do something to spruce it up. What if we take some lace from the old clothes in that box there and sew it on?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Don't look at me. I don't know the first thing about sewing.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Then it's up to me.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: You think I don't know you've never held a needle in your life?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Ahem.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: While I've never actually put it into practice, I have read a few books on the subject. I have an understanding of the basic concepts. And we have plenty of lace, anyway, we can do a test run on a towel first.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: And how long is that gonna take?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Maybe... one hour?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Anna!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Did you forget all the baking supplies we've gotta haul this afternoon?!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Yeah, me and Rosalind will bring the muscle, but you've gotta be there to tell us how much of what we're moving to where!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: This is a FOOD festival. Isn't the food the important part? Focus on the food first, and then if you've got time left over, screw around with your clothes and whatever. Doesn't that make sense?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You can take this if you're worried that you won't know what to move where.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: What's this paper?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Recipes. I stayed up all night preparing them. They have the desserts we'll be making and the ingredients needed to make them. Good luck.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: And while you're correct that our theming and decor is less important than the food, that doesn't mean appearances are entirely unimportant.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Suppose Natalya bakes some cookies that taste fine, but they come in random, unattractive shapes. Would you prefer to eat those, or Lada's?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: *Sigh*...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Whatever, there's no getting through to you.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I give up. You win. I'm gonna go find Rosalind.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Good luck. I'll be there to help you shortly.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Phew... we had a bit of a scare there, but I've got the lace nicely sewn onto the headband.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: (Forgive me, Lada, for breaking into your secret snack stash... I'll pay you back double tomorrow.)
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: It's two o'clock already...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I'd better go check on Sonya and Rosalind.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Natalya?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Good afternoon, Anna—I see you're in a hurry. May I ask to where?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Good afternoon, have you seen Rosalind?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Rosalind?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Yes, we were supposed to go with Sonya to move the flour and such this afternoon. But neither of us have been able to find her.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I do believe she's in the training room.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You saw her?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I can't say I laid my own eyes on her, but I did see two bottles of non-honeyed honey-flavored beverage at the door to the training room. To my knowledge, only Rosalind and Beehunter drink those.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Thank you very much, Natalya. You have a class in the afternoon, don't you?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I still have time, no need to rush.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Ah, but there is the matter of the application for the booth. You've asked that none of the surrounding booths serve beverages, and that yours should be close to the entrance, yes?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: That's correct. I would also like for the booth to be as large as possible, but I understand that's beyond our control.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: If there are too many participants, there simply won't be room for a large booth.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Indeed. Now then, I'll be sure to discuss the booth situation with Closure after my class.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Thank you very much.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Think nothing of it.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Although, I do believe this is the first time I've ever seen you so passionate about something besides books, Anna.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Is that a compliment?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I would like to think so.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Then I'll thank you once more.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Good luck, Anna.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: And the same to you, Natalya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: —Of course, to drag Rosalind out of the training room, you're going to need it.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Your prospects there are far more pessimistic, I believe.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Istina! What goes in the oven next?
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Cheese piroshki. They're already on the baking sheet, waiting for the last custard tart to come out.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Thanks for your help, Istina!
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Don't mention it.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I'm so glad you're here!
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: You've been helping set up the booth all day, and even went to fetch Leto for us, and got us fresh berries from the greenhouse with juuust the right acidity...
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: I thought you'd be really tired by now.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Well, I can't say it's been easy.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: So I think you'd better go back to your room and read for a bit! I can handle all this by myself!
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Of course, I'm sure you can do it.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But two heads are certainly more efficient than a single Gummy.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: You're really awesome, Istina.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I used to think just baking some tasty treats for everybody to enjoy at the festival would be enough.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: But you taught me good food alone doesn't cut it. To really make the festival perfect, you've gotta work out your theming, get a design, make everything match...
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: It's really awesome that you even think of this stuff, but you don't stop at the thinking, you actually come out and help us do everything. You find the time to lend Zima and little old Gummy a hand...
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: I never knew how awesome you were, Istina!
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: You're making me blush, Lada—
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Sorry, you're more comfortable with operator codenames now, yes?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Don't worry about it. Istina can call Gummy any name she wants!
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Thank you, Gummy.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: (To have Lada showering me with compliments like that... I really am blushing.)
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: (Especially considering how I just stole from her snack stash...)
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Oh, Gummy, there's something I have to tell you.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What is it, Istina?
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: While I was back at the room working on my outfit, I didn't have time to go to the canteen. I'm afraid I ate all the snacks you had hidden in the living room cabinet.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Oh? I don't remember putting any snacks there.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: But I found a package of cookies, they were pumpkin-flavored. I remember you were into pumpkin for a while.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Pumpkin, huh...? Let me think...
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Istina...
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Oh no... Gummy... why did your face turn so dour...?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Did those cookies taste really extra bitter and bad?
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: I... paired them with some coffee.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I burned those pumpkin cookies when I was baking in the canteen this morning.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: But it hurt my heart to think of throwing them away, so I put them in the bottom of the cabinet. I figured I could find some use for them.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: I mean, eating them won't do anything to you, but...
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: You've said enough, Gummy, I get it.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Just go home and get some rest! Leave it all to Gummy here. When everything's baked up, I'll call everyone to taste test!
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: With nothing to it but the traditional Ursus elements... hm... it feels a little shallow...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What if we added a little something else? Something like... a puzzle game?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: With just an outfit, a set of clothes, is there really a way to add deductive reasoning? Probably not.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But if we put it into the desserts—No, that won't work. It's not like we can make a puzzle out of them.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What about using the deductive elements as a sort of decoration?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Still a little off...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I've got it!
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Istina pulls a stack of books from the cabinet.
These books just might give us what we need.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: 'The Death of Ilyich, the Suspect', we can't well use this one.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Hm... let me think... with these books—
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: The idea is coming together, this should be possible.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Then we put the rest of them as padding underneath.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Need a few more clues... a chessboard, maybe? Let me see...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Welcome back, Sonya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What are you doing back here?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I had another idea. I need to revise the layout of our festival booth.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: The layout—Oh...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: (Whispers) I'm getting a headache.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I heard that.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Huh? 'The Death of Ilyich, the Suspect'? I borrowed this book.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I recommended it to you.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I forgot.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: So, do you remember the plot of the book?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Nope.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: What about the name of the killer?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Not coming to me.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: So what exactly did you read?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I never remember anything after I finish a novel.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Like, what's the point of remembering the plot of a book? Not like I'm gonna be a writer.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Forget it. This is my fault. I still have unrealistic expectations of you.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: (Whistles)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Now then, there will be a puzzle in our booth, and it derives from these books.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: 'Ten Little Durins', 'The Feranmut Four', 'Murder in Mossmead'... I feel like I've read these, but I also feel like I haven't.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You've been through all of them, and somehow didn't retain a thing.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I thought you'd be able to solve this puzzle, but now I find you can't.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: As if I even wanted to.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Not worth your time?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I just couldn't care less. I'm dead tired from hauling that crap all afternoon. The last thing I need is another pain in the ass.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: How about this? If you solve the puzzle on the day of the festival, I'll do your homework for you exactly once.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: You've been skipping Hypatia's class lately, haven't you?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Deal!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: On the other hand, if you can't solve it...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: We'll need a punishment. One I've not yet thought of.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Hmph. Punishment, huh? As if that scares me.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I'll be in my room.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You'll what?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What else am I gonna do? I told you, I'm dead tired. I'm going to bed.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I thought you'd at least take a book back to review. You have to prepare for the puzzle.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I know I'll be able to solve it when the time comes. Sleep is more important for now.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Well, good luck, Sonya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Thanks—
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Zima takes a few steps toward her room before turning back to Istina.
Actually, Anna, there's something I've been meaning to ask you since this morning.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Go ahead.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I've never seen you so passionate about something like this. You're even more into it than Lada is. You're totally committed to getting it perfect.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But why?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Any guesses?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Hm... to make Lada happy?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Making Lada happy is a delightful thing, but that's not the reason.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: To sell lots of sweets?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: You've forgotten, Sonya, everything at the festival is free.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: So what's the reason?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I just want to know what it feels like to go all in, for once.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: All in?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Have you lost your marbles? You're suddenly missing the old days?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: This is different, Sonya. Listen to me.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Back in those days...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Back in those days, we went all in and put it all on the line because if we slipped up even for a second, we were dead.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But this is different.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Now we're going all in on a happy little thing. How long has it been since we've busied ourselves with a happy little thing?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Think about it. The core of a food festival is a pleasant holiday atmosphere and the joy of eating. It doesn't get much more fun and relaxed than that.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What we did before, we did out of necessity. But now, laying it all on the line for a delightful little festival... I've never tried anything like that. And I want to.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: When the day of the festival comes, it'll probably be a lot of fun.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Zima shrugs.
I think you're having fun already.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Am I?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Yeah.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Welp, I may not get what's so much fun for you...
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But I hope it makes you happy.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Wowww! Soo many booths, and with so much food! I'm worried I can't eat it all...
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Calm down, Cardigan, the festival runs all day.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: Why are you following me at a time like this?!
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: It is precisely at a time like this that our little Lava needs to watch what she eats—
attributes.name: Hibiscus

attributes.content: What a uniquely sweet smell—
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Tell me about this thing. It's a custard tart, right?
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: And this one's a berry cake! I'd love to know the exact ratios at play in the recipe!
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: It would be my pleasure...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Treeaaaaats! I smell treeaaats!
attributes.name: Ceobe

attributes.content: Woooow! So many people! And so much food!
attributes.name: Ceobe

attributes.content: Little Cub made those snacks! They smell sooooo goooood!
attributes.name: Ceobe

attributes.content: Kay, slow down, no running!
attributes.name: Vulcan

attributes.content: How was the berry cake over there? Gummy only just brought out a tray and before I knew it, they'd all been snatched up.
attributes.name: Silence

attributes.content: Unusually delicious.
attributes.name: Ptilopsis

attributes.content: What do you think, Ifrit?
attributes.name: Silence

attributes.content: ...not spicy enough...
attributes.name: Ifrit

attributes.content: But the one with the light blue hair, she's dressed very pretty.
attributes.name: Ifrit

attributes.content: Watch this, Popukar—
attributes.name: Catapult

attributes.content: You threw the pastry up in the air, then caught it in your mouth on the way down—awesome!
attributes.name: Popukar

attributes.content: You wanna try? I can teach you—
attributes.name: Catapult

attributes.content: Gah!
attributes.name: Catapult

attributes.content: I don't want Popukar learning any stupid and dangerous tricks from you!
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: I've known for a while that Maggy has a very unique palate, but I never knew it went this far...
attributes.name: Mayer

attributes.content: Oh, is that some kind of puzzle thing over there?
attributes.name: Mayer

attributes.content: I've gotta check that out.
attributes.name: Mayer

attributes.content: What do you think of the puzzle Istina and the girls designed, Doctor?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.options: (Istina did a fine job.);(It's uncomplicated, but subtle.);(Just right for a food festival.)

attributes.content: Is something wrong, Doctor? Why are you so quiet?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Show a little restraint, Doctor, you've already eaten so much.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: The food festival's over...
attributes.name: Spot

attributes.content: I asked Midnight to wake me up, but the clown slipped out without a word.
attributes.name: Spot

attributes.content: Guess I shouldn't have stayed up all night reading comics.
attributes.name: Spot

attributes.content: What are those girls doing over there instead of packing up their booth?
attributes.name: Spot

attributes.content: I can't make out what they're saying—Huh? A shaved ice stand behind the stairs? I didn't even know it was there.
attributes.name: Spot

attributes.content: Yep, got plenty of cans left! Here you go!
attributes.name: Magallan

attributes.content: (Takes a deep breath)
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Graaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaagh!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Is that the legendary Ursus's Roar?
attributes.name: Spot

attributes.content: It's awe-inspiring.
attributes.name: Spot

attributes.text: Our booth was a big hit at the food festival.
We had a steady stream of operators coming to try things. Some came to eat, some came to try the puzzle, and some came just to look at my outfit...
Lada had to keep the ovens hot, and we went through all our spare supplies.
Sonya and Rosalind had to keep running back and forth between our booth and the kitchen.
Natalya explained all our treats to the customers. She talked her throat sore.
I had the most relaxed job, spending the day watching over the puzzle.

attributes.content: Istina speaks directly into the 'recording device for self-diagnosis and treatment of trauma using exposure therapy'.
I might have had a feeling about it, but I was surprised Sonya failed to solve the puzzle. The solution was so obvious.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: It was Rosalind's idea, but everyone agreed on the punishment. That Sonya would have to eat an entire bowl of Magallan's signature canned shaved ice.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Magallan's other flavors are plenty delicious.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But her signature canned shaved ice...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: How should I put this...? The look on Sonya's face as she brought the ice to her mouth...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Pfft... I can't even describe it.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What a wonderful day.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Standing in the crowd, looking at all the smiling faces around, listening to the delightful conversations that had nothing to do with me...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: While I normally wouldn't look to avoid such things, I also wouldn't be able to enjoy them.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But after throwing myself into this festival, all the noise and excitement started to mean something, it even became a reward for all my efforts.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Looking back, all that exhausting preparation was no trouble at all.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Really, going all out on a happy little thing was a ton of fun.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: In the old days, several of the middle schools in Chernobog would hold events like this.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: At the time, I found them pointless in comparison to reading a good book.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: So I was clever, avoided all the prep work, then spent the day of the event at home reading.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: It wasn't a big deal, honestly.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Something so typical. What's the point?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Don't these kinds of things happen every year?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Even after graduation, we could still attend as alumni, or the general public... why work hard for something like that?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I never imagined. I could never have imagined.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But it's true... there will never be another one.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Never, ever again.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Istina shakes her head vigorously.
So I spent a hundred and twenty percent of my energy on this food festival. Was that a sort of... memorialization?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: And the facts show that my efforts were worth it.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I've never experienced an event with so many people that was so enjoyable.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: If there's another such festival...
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: I dare not hope it could be as happy as this one.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: But I certainly want to try.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Now, that's enough for today—
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Anna, I'm home—
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Welcome back, Sonya.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Wasn't today fun?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Of course!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: But if we're talking about fun, I just found out there's still some food left, so I had the whole U.S.S.G. share it. And we've got a bit for you.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Didn't I see Natalya drink all the borscht? What could be left?
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: What else? Magallan's cans!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I'm going to bed. Good night, Sonya. Sweet dreams—
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: You're not going anywhere. You're the only one who hasn't had any—
attributes.name: Zima
